Description

SOFTWARE ENGINEER RAIL SIGNALING (Entry-level)

REQUISITION NUMBER:
Description

Bombardier Transportation is a world-wide leader in rail technology. From mainline to metro, light rail to locomotives, our strategy is one of continuous development that provides the most effective and innovative rail solutions for today and tomorrow!

Rail Control Solutions (RCS) is Bombardier Transportation’s signaling division. RCS is focused on optimizing the flow of trains and delivering innovative signaling systems which enable the safe and efficient operation of rail networks and trains. A career within RCS enables you to work closely with our world-class engineers and learn more about how your field of study and interests can be applied to the transportation industry so you can create better ways to move the world!

Our Software Engineers develop automatic train control (ATC) software for rail vehicles or track (wayside) applications to deliver products, tools, and systems for driver-less train operation and control. This is a hands-on developer role where you code, load, and see the impact of your work! Your software will enhance safety, increase reliability, and create environmentally sustainable solutions for mass transit rail systems.

In your role you will:

Design software tools and simulation systems using C, C#, C++, and/or Java;
Develop and analyze software requirements to satisfy product, project, and safety requirements;
Define systems architecture and interfaces;
Develop software testing procedures, programming, and documentation;
Support all phases of in-house and on-site systems testing and commissioning;
Generate technical deliverables to ensure schedule and quality of work are maintained.

Qualifications

As our ideal candidate:

You possess a Bachelor's Degree in Software, Computer, or Electrical Engineering or related discipline;
You possess academic, internship, or co-op experience in a software or embedded software development position or related engineering role;
You must be able to program in C, C#, and/or C++ (Java development a plus);
You demonstrate a strong understanding of software development, serial and network communication, and software processes;
You have experience troubleshooting and diagnosing issues;
Hardware programming experience will be considered a plus;
Permanent work authorization in the U.S. is required.
You can operate independently while establishing strong working relationships with co-workers and cross-functional teams;
You possess strong organizational and prioritization skills;
You demonstrate critical attention to detail and deadlines, and are self-motivated;
You possess the ability to adapt well to change in direction and priorities in a project and deadline-oriented environment;
Your written and verbal English communication skills are excellent.

Travel advisory: You may be required to travel domestically and/or internationally as required by business needs.

We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those under consideration will be contacted.

Join us at careers.bombardier.com

